---
title: "RxCheck : Searching for an NCPDP Taxonomy Code"
parent: "RxConsole User Guide"
nav_order: 65
---
1. Click on the *NCPDP Taxonomy Code Mapping* button, located on the left-hand side of the screen.

2. Locate the code mapping you are searching for by either:

   1. Scrolling through the list of codes displayed on the screen and sifting through the pages by clicking the arrows under the *Code Mapping* table.
   2. Locate the mapping directly by entering the taxonomy code, description, or PMIX role into the search box labeled, *Filter Mapping* in the top right corner of the screen.

